<li>Use R to change your working directory to some other place. What do you notice in the RStudio Files window?</li>
<li>Use RStudio to change back to your previous working directory (r-intro) What do you notice in the RStudio Console?</li>
</ul>
</blockquote>
</div>
<div id="rstudio-script-editor" class="section level3">
<h3><span class="header-section-number">1.5.2</span> RStudio Script Editor</h3>
<p>Because we want to keep our code and workflow, it is better to type
the commands we want in the script editor, and save the script. This way, there
is a complete record of what we did, and anyone (including our future selves!)
can easily replicate the results on their computer.</p>
<p>Perhaps one of the most important aspects of making your code comprehensible for others and your future self is adding comments about why you did something. You can write comments directly in your script, and tell R not no execute those words simply by putting a hashtag (<code>#</code>) before you start typing the comment.</p>
